criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  mother aged 18-40 years;

          -  first-time mother, full-term and singleton pregnancy;

          -  the Hamilton Anxiety Scale(HAMA) score ≥14;

          -  the birth with no intrapartum complications;

          -  Apgar score > 8 at the first, fifth, and tenth minutes after birth.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  any mental illness besides anxiety, maternal medical illness, hypertension, advanced
             liver disease, renal failure, cancer, valvular heart disease, heart failure, stroke,
             atrial fibrillation, peripheral arterial disease, and other severe diseases;

          -  preterm infants (< 37 weeks gestation);

          -  multiple births;

          -  infants with congenital anomalies, signs of illness, or high-risk factors.
